track_notes: Park either in CP at SK 048 869 (Â£3-50 all day) or roadside if there is room. Cross  bridge (toilets R). Follow road to L. Continue to X, straight ahead up hill.Loop around farm. Straight up hill. After several stiles tackle Kinder Low end. Good steps. Good path now continues all the way to meet Pennine Way. Turn L to reach large cairn and Trig Point. You are now in AZ. True summit is 750m NE - only 3m higher.

Either park at Bowden Bridge Car Park (Now Â£4.50 all day cash only) or park along Kinder Road for free.

This route takes you up to Kinder Low via Edale road, then across the fields to a false summit, before ascending the stairs up to the plateau. You are then in the activation zone (Which is quite large).

The return route takes you via Kinder Spout, and down the side of Kinder reservoir.
